# /pair-agent — Browser Sharing

> **Note:** This skill requires the gstack browse daemon, which is not installed
> in this version of gstack. The pair-agent feature enabled one AI agent to share
> its browser session with another agent over a local HTTP server.
>
> To use multi-agent browser sharing, you would need a version of gstack with
> the browse binary installed. This feature has been removed from the default
> distribution to simplify the install footprint.

If you need to share state between agents, consider:
- Sharing file paths to screenshots you've taken with Claude's native screenshot tools
- Passing structured JSON outputs between agent sessions
- Using a shared git branch as coordination layer
